com.unvired.chyme.api

Class SAPEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.unvired.chyme.api.SAPEvent

  • public class SAPEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    The SAPEvent class is an abstraction of a business event or trigger generated in SAP An event in SAP could be the creation, updating or deletion of a business entity in SAP.

    An event from SAP has the following components.

    • System ID - ID of an SAP system to identity the system in a complex SAP landscape. For Ex: IED
    • BOR Object - Business Object Repository identification of an entity. For Ex: BUS2012 for Purchase Order
    • Event - The event on the BOR object. For Ex: RELEASE_STEP_CREATED on BUS2012
    • Object Key - Unique key of the BOR object to identify it in the SPA system
    • Sender - The business module or logical name in the SAP system generating the event
    • Data - Contextual data from the SAP system as a json or plain text for use in the the BOT function
